<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 7:59PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Garfield and southwestern McCone Counties through 900 PM MDT...
At 759 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Cohagen, or 20 miles southeast of Jordan, moving
northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cohagen, Nelson Creek Rec Area, Flowing Wells Rest Area and Van
Norman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
